Eyes: anterior eye row procurved, posterior eye row recurved. Periocular pigmentation only present in anterior eye row and strongly marked on AME. PME reduced and PLE slightly integumentary. Eye sizes and interocular distances: AME 0.28; ALE 0.345; PME 0.21; PLE 0.333; AME–AME 0.222; AME–ALE 0.148; PME–PME 0.83; PME–PLE 0.12; ALE–PLP 0.111. Ocular tubercle reduced, width 1.85; length 0.9; clypeus lacking (
Fig. 6E
). Labium: length 1.1; width 1.9; with 11 cuspules. Maxilla inner corner with approximately 95 cuspules (
Fig. 6F
). Cheliceral promargin with nine teeth (proximal to distal: first medium, second-third large, fourth-fifth medium, sixth-eighth large, ninth small). Sternum length 4.0. Sigillae semicircular, third and fourth pairs hardly visible; fourth pair once its length from the margin (
Fig. 6B
).

