Genitalia: spermathecae paired, slightly fused, broad at base. Receptacles without neck defined by interior or exterior margin; bent laterally and tapering distally (
Fig. 6G
).

Genitalia variation: the general shape of the spermathecae is similar, but not strongly bent laterally (
Fig. 6H
).
